@tiangolo Any chance we could get either a weaker pinning, or at least `<=1.1.1` (the current release)? This would enable use with the new pydantic mypy plugin.

Weaker pinning would make it easier to upgrade to bug-fixed versions of pydantic, and my suspicion is that when the fastapi community upgrades to using pydantic v1, there will be a lot more stress-testing of pydantic v1 that may quickly flush out any existing bugs.

But if you want to wait and see if pydantic is able to live up to its backwards-compatibility promises that's fine with me.

